Z8DIFc3QRgkoQ-IP9UeJ_g
Been here 3 times for Electric Daisy Carnival! The best times of my life! It's an experience like none other, you'll feels ways you've never felt before, and see things you'll never see again.   You walk in through the tunnels and hear the echos of the music from all the stages, building the anticipation to the extreme. Then you walk out and it's just a beautiful wonderland of lights, music, friends and energy! It's hard to not be overwhelmed by emotions.   Make sure to take the time to see EVERYTHING. The black light rooms, the art, the  bars, the parades, the rides, the fun houses, the firework shows...THERE IS SO MUCH!   So many amazing artists.... Armin Van Buuren, Kaskade, Swedish House Mafia, Above & Beyond, Dash Berlin... I can't even right now. Just thinking about this place makes me feel so happy. Try to see a few artists you've never seen, you'll discover so many new people!   Okay, okay, the serious stuff. There are free water refill stations, so make sure to hydrate! There is an entire section dedicated to medical to make sure everyone is safe. LOTS of cops, but they don't hassle anyone - I've even seen some dancing! Some will trade kandi with you too!  There are food options and fruit stands as well. Check out the merchandise booths too and pick something up! Security is pretty tight, so just make sure to follow the rules :) The lines to get in can be long, but they go fast when everyone pays attention and has things ready. There are also misters to keep you cool, as this event is in June and it gets hot! Shuttles are the way to go as well in terms of transportation. I've heard bad things about cars being broken into and/or stolen from the lots :(  Experience EDC for yourself at least once, it is the event of a lifetime!!

