Had an absolute blast here at the Superbowl!   This place is incredible looking inside and out! Whoever designed this was very creative.   Lots of parking lots, make sure you pay attention. There are signs up saying "no tailgating," but I saw plenty of people doing so for the game, so I don't know if they just allowed it because it was the Superbowl or what.   There isn't really a bad seat. Our family was split up as we weren't able to find 5 tickets together; 3 of us in the lower level end zone, and 2 up top in the 400 level in the end zone. I sat in both levels and thought the views were great. There are two huge jumbo screens too.  Pretty decent selection of food vendors. Lots of beer. Expect your normal stadium pricing.  I also heard they have AC during the summer!   Would definitely come back for another game here if I had the chance!

